==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Mow
<hw>Mow</hw> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Mowed</conjf> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧d)</pr>;
<pos>p. p.</pos> <conjf>Mowed</conjf> or <conjf>Mown</conjf>
<pr>(m⟦omac⟧n)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Mowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>mowen</ets>,
<ets>mawen</ets>, AS. <ets>m⟦amac⟧wan</ets>; akin to D.
<ets>maaijen</ets>, G. <ets>m⟦aum⟧hen</ets>, OHG. <ets>m⟦amac⟧jan</ets>,
Dan. <ets>meie</ets>, L. <ets>metere</ets> to reap, mow, Gr.
<grk>'ama^n</grk>. Cf. <er>Math</er>, <er>Mead</er> a meadow,
<er>Meadow</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cut down, as grass, with a
scythe or machine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cut the grass from; <as>as, to <ex>mow</ex> a
meadow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To cut down; to cause to fall in rows or masses, as
in mowing grass; -- with <xex>down</xex>; <as>as, a discharge of
grapeshot <ex>mows</ex> down whole ranks of men</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 6 ====
HEADWORD: Mow
<hw>Mow</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To cut grass, etc., with a scythe,
or with a machine; to cut grass for hay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 7 ====
HEADWORD: Mow
<hw>Mow</hw> <pr>(mou)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>mowe</ets>,
AS. <ets>m⟦umac⟧ga</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A heap or mass of hay
or of sheaves of grain stowed in a barn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The place in a barn where hay or grain in the sheaf
is stowed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 8 ====
HEADWORD: Mow
<hw>Mow</hw> <pr>(mou)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To lay, as hay or
sheaves of grain, in a heap or mass in a barn; to pile and stow
away.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mowburn</ent>⟦br⟧
